  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Our `expectEvent` helper currently comes in two variants: `expectEvent.inLogs` and `expectEvent.inTransaction`. As far as I can tell, we only need one of the two. `inTransaction` was suggested by @nventuro as the one to keep.\r\n\r\nI'd also reconsider whether it should be an async function. It seems like it would make sense as a sync function. We can expect a receipt as the argument and we wouldn't need to `await` it.",
